init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're afraid to move, afraid to breathe, afraid to do anything.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee, sensing your fear, flies off your shoulder and lands on your hand.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Your Majesty, what are your orders?" it asks again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look at the bee, then at your hand, then back at the bee.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You realize that you have a choice.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can either believe the lies you've been told your entire life, or you can take a chance and do something you've never done before.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee looks at you and says, "Because you are my king.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are the king of all bees.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are the king of the hive.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look at the bee and say, "I don't believe you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'm not the king of the hive.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'm not the king of all bees.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'm not the king of anything."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee flies off your hand and lands on the ground.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It then starts to move around the ground, gathering up all the other bees in the area.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It gathers up hundreds of bees, all of them buzzing around you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee then flies back up to you and lands on your hand.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look at the bees and say, "I don't have any disciples.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look at the bee and say, "I don't understand.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bees all buzz in excitement.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bees fly off your hand and head towards Soeurette's apartment.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You watch them go, and you're filled with a sense of power.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You've never had the ability to control anything before, but now you can control the bees.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can make her pay for all the times she's been rude to you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They fly in through her window and start stinging her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She screams and tries to swat them away, but there are too many of them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She runs around her apartment, trying to escape them, but they keep coming.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She falls to the ground, and the bees continue to sting her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She looks up at you and says, "Why are you doing this to me?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I've never done anything to you!"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You smile and say, "You've been rude to me for years.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I've never been able to get back at you, but now I can.
